      "content": "One dose of pseudoephedrine is unlikely to cause major harm to your baby, but it is not without risk, especially at 20 weeks when blood flow to the placenta is critical. It is always safer to consult your doctor first, but if you are in severe distress right now, consider using saline nasal irrigation or a doctor-approved steroid spray as a temporary measure to ease breathing. Please try to stay calm and hydrate, as stress can also worsen sinus congestion.",
